sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K646007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 promoter with Heme oxygenase and Rhizobium radiobacter bacteriophytochrome
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is an assembly of an Rhizobium radiobacter/Agrobacterium tumefaciens isolated bacteriophytochrome gene with a Synechocytis heme oxygenase 1 gene under a T7 promoter. The bacteriophytochrome gene produces a protein that interacts with Biliverdin, a chromophore. The chromophore is produced by heme oxygenase oxidation of heme in the heme metabolic pathway to produce the biliverdin. Sequence contains a Ribosome Binding Site. Sequence from National Center for Biotechnology.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Dubow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Origin from genomic DNA and 2011 kit plates.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K646004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Using parts BBa_K646000 and BBa_I712074, a T7 promoted Hemeoxygenase was created by digesting the T7 biobrick with S and P and ligating it to the HO insert also digested with S and P.
Successful expression should result in green colonies due to the presence of biliverdin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Dubow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I712074
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 promoter (strong promoter from T7 bacteriophage)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T7 promoter is very specific promoter which is transcribed only by specific T7 RNA polymerase. Usually this promoter is used in expression systems where T7 promoter is cotransfected with T7 RNA polymerase. That ensures strong transcription of desired genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Rok Gaber

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: HO1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Synechocystis hemeoxygenase with a Ribosome Binding Site (RBS), oxidises Heme into biliverdin which absorbs light in the 360 nm and 650 nm wavelength producing a green colouration.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edward Moh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The gene was digested with X and S before ligation, several ligations were done to ensure correct orientation.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: AT-Bph
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Bacteriophotochrome from Argobacterium tumefaciens (Now Rhizobium radiobacter), that binds to biliverdin to produce a complex that absorbs far red light which catalyses isomerisation to produce a spectral change.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Dubow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From 2010 Macquarie Team, isolated from Genomic DNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Contains two internal Pst1 RE sites.
